==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neologist
<hw>Ne*ol"o*gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧ologiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who introduces
new words or new senses of old words into a language.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> verbarian.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An innovator in any doctrine or system of belief,
especially in theology; one who introduces or holds doctrines subversive
of supernatural or revealed religion; a rationalist,
so-called.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neologistical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Neologistic</ent>⟦br⟧
